A former Women Leader of the Lagos State and South West chapters of the All Progressives Congress, Kemi Nelson is dead. She was also a member of the Governance Advisory Council in Lagos State. The former Executive Director of the Nigeria Social Insurance Trust Fund, died on Sunday, 17 July, 2022 after a protracted battle with cancer. She was said to have been unwell for a while and had undergone treatments at different hospitals. Nelson was a former Commissioner for Womenâ€™s Affairs and Poverty Alleviation in Lagos under Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu administration. She was born on February 9, 1956. The deceased politician is survived by her three children.